==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Antanaclasis
<hw>Ant`an*a*cla"sis</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<?/; <grk>'anti`</grk>/ + <grk>'ana`klasis</grk> a bending back and
breaking. See <er>Anaclastic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A figure which consists in repeating the same word in
a different sense; as, Learn some <xex>craft</xex> when young, that when
old you may live without <xex>craft</xex>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A
repetition of words beginning a sentence, after a long parenthesis; as,
Shall that heart (which not only feels them, but which has all motions
of life placed in them), <xex>shall that heart</xex>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antanagoge</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
